         "output": "     1\t---\n     2\tname: google-forms\n                   
   3\tdescription: Create and manage Google Forms via Google Apps Script Web    
   App.\n     4\ttags: [\"Google\", \"Forms\", \"Automation\"]\n                
   5\tversion: 2.3.0\n     6\t---\n     7\t\n     8\t# Google Forms Skill\n     
   9\t\n    10\tCreate and manage Google Forms through a Google Apps Script     
   Web App.\n    11\t\n    12\t## What this skill uses\n    13\t- Web-app       
   flow only for normal use\n    14\t- No OAuth\n    15\t- One required env     
   var: `GFORMS`\n    16\t- Optional env var if your deployment enforces it:    
   `GFORMS_SECRET`\n    17\t\n    18\t## From scratch setup\n    19\t1. Open    
   [script.new](https://script.new)\n    20\t2. Paste the full contents of      
   `~/gform_automation/scripts/appscript_code.gs`\n    21\t3. Save the          
   script\n    22\t4. Deploy → New deployment → Web app\n    23\t5. Set         
   Execute as: Me\n    24\t6. Set Who has access: Anyone\n    25\t7. Copy the   
   deployed Web App URL into `~/gform_automation/.env`\n    26\t8. If your      
   script uses a shared secret, generate one and store it in both the Apps      
   Script code and `GFORMS_SECRET`\n    27\t\n    28\t## Local config\n         
   29\tCreate `~/gform_automation/.env`:\n    30\t```bash\n    31\tcat >        
   ~/gform_automation/.env <<'EOF'\n                                            
   32\tGFORMS=https://script.google.com/macros/s/YOUR_WEBAPP_ID/exec\n          
   33\t# Optional, only if your deployed script checks a secret:\n    34\t#     
   GFORMS_SECRET=YOUR_SHARED_SECRET\n    35\tEOF\n    36\t```\n    37\t\n       
   38\tLoad it in shell sessions with:\n    39\t```bash\n    40\tset -a\n       
   41\tsource ~/gform_automation/.env\n    42\tset +a\n    43\t```\n            
   44\t\n    45\t## Core workflow\n    46\tAll actions go through the web       
   app.\n    47\t\n    48\t### Create a form\n    49\tWrites return a           
   redirect first. Capture the `Location` header, then fetch that URL for the   
   JSON response.\n    50\t```bash\n                                            
   51\tpayload='{\"action\":\"create\",\"title\":\"My                           
   Form\",\"description\":\"Optional description\",\"questions\":[...]}'\n      
   52\t\n    53\tresp=$(curl -s -i -X POST \"$GFORMS\" \\\n    54\t  -H         
   'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n    55\t  --data-binary                 
   \"$payload\")\n    56\t\n    57\tloc=$(printf '%s' \"$resp\" | sed -n        
   's/^location: //Ip' | tr -d '\\r')\n    58\tcurl -s \"$loc\"\n               
   59\t```\n    60\t\n    61\tIf your deployment requires a secret, include     
   it in the JSON body:\n    62\t```bash\n                                      
   63\tpayload='{\"secret\":\"'\"$GFORMS_SECRET\"'\",\"action\":\"create\",..   
   .}'\n    64\t```\n    65\t\n    66\t### List forms\n    67\t```bash\n        
   68\tcurl -s -L -X POST \"$GFORMS\" -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d    
   '{\"action\":\"list\"}'\n    69\t```\n    70\t\n    71\t### Get form\n       
   72\t```bash\n    73\tcurl -s -L -X POST \"$GFORMS\" -H 'Content-Type:        
   application/json' -d '{\"action\":\"get\",\"formId\":\"FORM_ID\"}'\n         
   74\t```\n    75\t\n    76\t### Add questions\n    77\t```bash\n              
   78\tcurl -s -L -X POST \"$GFORMS\" \\\n    79\t  -H 'Content-Type:           
   application/json' \\\n    80\t  -d                                           
   '{\"action\":\"addQuestions\",\"formId\":\"FORM_ID\",\"questions\":[{\"typ   
   e\":\"rating\",\"title\":\"Rate                                              
   1-10\",\"required\":true,\"scaleMax\":10}]}'\n    81\t```\n    82\t\n        
   83\t### Get responses\n    84\t```bash\n    85\tcurl -s -L -X POST           
   \"$GFORMS\" -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d                           
   '{\"action\":\"responses\",\"formId\":\"FORM_ID\"}'\n    86\t```\n           
   87\t\n    88\t## Question building blocks\n    89\tUse these generic         
   patterns when building forms:\n    90\t\n    91\t- `text`: short free-text   
   answer\n    92\t- `paragraph`: longer free-text answer\n    93\t-            
   `multiple_choice`: one answer from a list\n    94\t- `checkbox`: many        
   answers from a list\n    95\t- `dropdown`: one answer from a compact         
   list\n    96\t- `rating`: numeric rating from 1 to N\n    97\t- `date`:      
   date picker\n    98\t- `time`: time picker\n    99\t- `grid`: matrix-style   
   question with rows and columns\n   100\t- `email`: email field with          
   validation\n   101\t\n   102\t### Generic examples\n   103\t```json\n        
   104\t{\"type\":\"text\",\"title\":\"Your name\",\"required\":true}\n         
   105\t```\n   106\t\n   107\t```json\n                                        
   108\t{\"type\":\"multiple_choice\",\"title\":\"Which option best             
   fits?\",\"required\":true,\"options\":[\"Option A\",\"Option B\",\"Option    
   C\"]}\n   109\t```\n   110\t\n   111\t```json\n                              
   112\t{\"type\":\"checkbox\",\"title\":\"Select all that                      
   apply\",\"required\":false,\"options\":[\"Option A\",\"Option B\",\"Option   
   C\"]}\n   113\t```\n   114\t\n   115\t```json\n                              
   116\t{\"type\":\"rating\",\"title\":\"Rate this                              
   item\",\"required\":true,\"scaleMax\":10}\n   117\t```\n   118\t\n           
   119\t## Supported question types\n   120\t| Type | Fields | Notes |\n        
   121\t|------|--------|-------|\n   122\t| `text` | `title`, `required` |     
   Short answer |\n   123\t| `paragraph` | `title`, `required` | Long answer    
   |\n   124\t| `multiple_choice` | `title`, `required`, `options[]` | Radio    
   buttons |\n   125\t| `checkbox` | `title`, `required`, `options[]` |         
   Multi-select |\n   126\t| `dropdown` | `title`, `required`, `options[]` |    
   Dropdown list |\n   127\t| `rating` | `title`, `required`, `scaleMax` |      
   1-N stars/hearts/thumbs |\n   128\t| `date` | `title`, `required` | Date     
   picker |\n   129\t| `time` | `title`, `required` | Time picker |\n           
   130\t| `grid` | `title`, `required`, `rows[]`, `cols[]` | Grid table |\n     
   131\t| `email` | `title`, `required` | Email validation |\n   132\t\n        
   133\t## Rating questions\n   134\tGoogle Forms rating questions use          
   `addRatingItem()`. They support 1–10 levels and three icon styles: STAR,     
   HEART, THUMB_UP.\n   135\t\n   136\t```json\n   137\t{\n   138\t             
   \"type\": \"rating\",\n   139\t  \"title\": \"Rate this section\",\n         
   140\t  \"required\": true,\n   141\t  \"scaleMax\": 10,\n   142\t            
   \"ratingIcon\": \"STAR\"\n   143\t}\n   144\t```\n   145\t\n   146\t##       
   Deploy checklist\n   147\tAfter editing `scripts/appscript_code.gs`:\n       
   148\t1. Save in Apps Script\n   149\t2. Deploy → Manage deployments → Edit   
   → New version → Deploy\n   150\t3. Copy the new Web App URL into             
   `~/gform_automation/.env` if it changed\n   151\t4. If your script uses a    
   secret, update `GFORMS_SECRET` to match\n   152\t5. If `Page Not Found`      
   appears, verify access is still set to Anyone\n   153\t\n   154\t## Known    
   pitfalls\n   155\t1. Saving code does not update the web app; you must       
   deploy a new version.\n   156\t2. Create/update actions may redirect. For    
   writes, capture the `Location` header and fetch that URL.\n   157\t3. Use    
   `addRatingItem()` for numbered 1-10 rating questions instead of              
   `addScaleItem()`.\n   158\t4. If a command times out, retry once after a     
   short pause; avoid backgrounding the write path.\n   159\t5. If you use a    
   shared secret in your deployment, the request body must include the          
   matching `secret` field.\n   160\t\n",                                       
